## Hardware & Infrastructure

**Deployment:** White Plains, NY → Athens, Greece ~Mar 11–May 15, 2026. Flatio booking (195/19 Mbps). Flights purchased. First month rent paid ($1,000).

**Streaming Core:** GIGABYTE AERO X16 (RTX 5070, 32GB) → OBS/NVENC · Elgato Facecam MK.2 (primary stream camera) · Elgato Stream Deck + (scene switching) · Elgato Key Light Neo · Blue Yeti Nano (voice) · Sony WH-1000XM5 (monitoring) · KLIM Cooling Pad · iPad for chat (WiFi, zero laptop ports used)

**Camera (Content/BTS):** GoPro HERO13 Black + accessories

**Storage:** SanDisk 2TB SSD (primary) · Samsung T9 2TB SSD (backup) · microSD 256GB + 64GB

**Monitors:** ASUS ZenScreen 15.6" (non-streaming productivity monitor — requires USB-C/DP Alt Mode, which conflicts with the Anker hub during streams). Samsung 22" purchased Dec 11 ($75.85) but not in active rig — did not work well operationally.

**Internet:** GL.iNet GL-MT6000 (dual-WAN, router-level failover) · Netgear M7 Pro 5G (backup WAN on router WAN2) · Bingfu MIMO Antenna · USB-C Ethernet Adapter. **Note:** Speedify is installed but functionally inactive — current topology has both WANs behind the router, so the laptop sees one LAN interface. Router handles failover directly. For Speedify to work, M7 Pro would need direct USB tethering to laptop as a second physical interface.

**Power:** Anker 737 24k mAh (laptop + power-only devices like KLIM) · TalentCell Mini UPS (router stack) · ELECOM NESTOUT 15k mAh (emergency)

**Charging:** Anker 100W 3-Port · 7-in-1 Hub (PD passthrough + 2×USB-A + card reader) · Prime 240W Cable

**Travel:** Tortuga Pro 40L · Alpaka Elements Tech Case · Cable Lock · ABUS Padlocks

**Software:** OBS Studio (NVENC) · Restream Standard (~$16/mo, simulcast YouTube + Twitch) · ExpressVPN · DigitalOcean VPS (~$6/mo, available for future 24/7 radio, on standby)

**OBS Scenes:** Outside Inn Warmup (Holdt animation + LofiLoop.wav 100% + countdown timer + patron roll) → Writing Stream (facecam + Notion, music 20–30%) → Gaming Stream (facecam + game, music 20–30% or off) → Cooldown (Holdt animation + music 100%). All one-button via Stream Deck. The 70:07 bookend opens and closes every live stream. 24/7 ambient radio deferred until headless OBS on VPS + deeper content catalog justify it (~April 2026+). VPS infrastructure stays available.

**Uptime:** 99.9% target — wired primary + 5G failover at router level + battery backup on laptop and router. Floor: laptop + webcam + mic + 10 Mbps upload on ethernet = reliable stream.

**Day-one validation (Mar 3):** Core stack performed. 11h39m radio run without a drop. Live stream went out on YouTube and Twitch via Restream. Four issues encountered and resolved in real time (YouTube stream key reset, Restream channel toggle, FFmpeg suspension, YouTube Studio dashboard confusion — all documented in OIS Hardware & Software Master).

## Tech & Operational Advantage

Evan's background eliminates contractor needs for ecommerce, streaming infra, analytics, and tooling — saving est. $2,000–5,000/month vs. non-technical founder.

- **Ecommerce:** 8+ payment types at SKIMS, OMS/ERP/WMS architecture, 600k+ order-day scale build-vs-buy decisions
- **Streaming:** Full OBS/Restream stack self-configured. Router-level dual-WAN failover. 99.6% uptime experience at SKIMS peak events. Day-one tech issues diagnosed and resolved without outside help.
- **Data:** Built Watchtower (CFO dashboard), Apollo (CX platform, 94% error reduction), Lighthouse (retail ops)
- **AI:** Netomi chatbot (16% ticket reduction), GitHub Copilot knowledge base (18% faster engineering). Claude pair-programming used to build animation pipeline, countdown timer, and patron roll overlay in 48 hours pre-launch.
- **Agile:** Scrum from scratch at SKIMS, team ~5→40+, Jira for 116 users, 3 Notion workspaces → 1
- **Expert networks:** GLG, AlphaSights, Guidepoint at $399/hr — same expertise deployed on OIS at zero cost

